{"definitions":[{"type":"adjective","definition":"to be desired or approved of.","example":"it's good that he's back to his old self","image_url":null},{"type":"adjective","definition":"having the required qualities; of a high standard.","example":"a good restaurant","image_url":null},{"type":"adjective","definition":"possessing or displaying moral virtue.","example":"her father was a good man","image_url":null},{"type":"adjective","definition":"giving pleasure; enjoyable or satisfying.","example":"the streets fill up with people looking for a good time","image_url":null},{"type":"adjective","definition":"thorough.","example":"now is the time to have a really good clear-up","image_url":null},{"type":"adjective","definition":"valid.","example":"the ticket is good for travel from May to September","image_url":null},{"type":"noun","definition":"that which is morally right; righteousness.","example":"a mysterious balance of good and evil","image_url":null},{"type":"noun","definition":"benefit or advantage to someone or something.","example":"he convinces his father to use his genius <b>for the good of</b> mankind","image_url":null},{"type":"noun","definition":"merchandise or possessions.","example":"imports of luxury goods","image_url":null},{"type":"adverb","definition":"well.","example":"my mother could never cook this good","image_url":null},{"type":"adjective","definition":"used in conjunction with the name of God or a related expression as an exclamation of extreme surprise or anger.","example":"good heavens!","image_url":null}],"word":"good","pronunciation":"ɡo͝od"}